In order to obtain information about the chemical speciation and elemental composition, X-ray photoelectron spectroscopy (XPS) measurements were recorded. Carbon, nitrogen and oxygen were present in all samples and additional sulphur on cysteamine and POS-CYSTE surface. Figure S2 a and b (see ESM) shows the N1s and S2p spectra. In the ethylenediamine samples, the peak is analyzed into two components at binding energies of 400.3 eV, due to amine groups (N-C), and 401.8 eV attributed to different bonding environment ((NR4)+ or oxidic nitrogen species because of the aqueous solution [47,48]). In the cysteamine sample only the component at 401.8 is present. In the POS sample, the binding energy of N1s is centred at 400.8 eV (higher than in the amine groups) and can be attributed to quaternary nitrogen or to both imide (O = C–N–C = O) and amide (–N– C = O) groups [49]. In the POS-ETH and POS-CYSTE surfaces the N1s peak consists of the components that exist on both POS and cysteamine or ethylenediamine samples. Moreover, in the ethylenediamine and POS-ETH samples a low intensity peak at ~ 408 eV, denoted with the arrows, is assigned to nitrates. In the S2p spectra, two main peaks were observed at 163.65 eV and 164.83 eV assigned to the 2p3/2 and 2p1/2 S–C bond, respectively. Additionally, in the cysteamine sample a low intensity peak at ~ 168 eV is present due to oxidized sulphur species. Figure S3 a,b (ESM) shows the corresponding C1s core level spectra of ethylenediamine and cysteamine samples. Each C1s peak is analyzed into four components: sp3 C–C/C-N bonds, hydroxyls/epoxides C-O(H), carbonyls (C = O) and carboxyls (O = C-OH) [50]. Fig. S3 c-e (ESM) shows the C1s peak of POS and the ethylenediamine, cysteamine hybrid nanostructures. An additional component assigned to conjugated sp2 C = C carbon bonds is present due to the presence of carbon dots. Table 1
                         shows the % components composition of each sample. From Table 1 is concluded that when cysteamine and ethylenediamine are added to POS, the concentration of nitrogen is increased. Additionally, sulphur is present on the POS-CYSTE surface when cysteamine is added to POS. From the C1s peak deconvolution (Table 2
                        ), the concentration of C-N bonds increases and sp2 C = C component is present on the POS-ETH and POS-CYSTE hybrids surface due to the addition of ethylenediamine and cysteamine.
